      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The French Revolution was a transformative period in modern history, marked by the storming of the Bastille on July 14, 1789, a pivotal event that symbolized the people's rejection of absolute monarchy. As economic hardship and food shortages intensified, the National Assembly, representing the Third Estate, adopted the Tennis Court Oath, vowing to continue their work on a new constitution despite King Louis XVI's orders to disband. This bold move set the stage for the eventual adoption of the Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen in August 1789, which enshrined the principles of liberty, equality, and fraternity. Meanwhile, Maximilien Robespierre, a leading figure in the Jacobin faction, seized control of the Committee of Public Safety in 1793, leading to the Reign of Terror, a period of extreme violence and repression that lasted from 1793 to 1794. The queen, Marie Antoinette, was executed by guillotine in October 1793, while Napoleon Bonaparte, a brilliant and ambitious military leader, rose to power in 1799, marking the end of the Revolution and paving the way for a new era of French history.",
